From: Mikulas Patocka <mpatocka@redhat.com>
Date: Tue, 13 Aug 2024 12:38:51 +0200
Subject: dm suspend: return -ERESTARTSYS instead of -EINTR
Patch-mainline: v6.11-rc4
Git-commit: 1e1fd567d32fcf7544c6e09e0e5bc6c650da6e23
References: git-fixes

This commit changes device mapper, so that it returns -ERESTARTSYS
instead of -EINTR when it is interrupted by a signal (so that the ioctl
can be restarted).

The manpage signal(7) says that the ioctl function should be restarted if
the signal was handled with SA_RESTART.

Signed-off-by: Mikulas Patocka <mpatocka@redhat.com>
Cc: stable@vger.kernel.org
Acked-by: Martin Wilck <mwilck@suse.com>
---
 drivers/md/dm.c |    4 ++--
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+), 2 deletions(-)

--- a/drivers/md/dm.c
+++ b/drivers/md/dm.c
@@ -2557,7 +2557,7 @@ static int dm_wait_for_bios_completion(s
 			break;
 
 		if (signal_pending_state(task_state, current)) {
-			r = -EINTR;
+			r = -ERESTARTSYS;
 			break;
 		}
 
@@ -2582,7 +2582,7 @@ static int dm_wait_for_completion(struct
 			break;
 
 		if (signal_pending_state(task_state, current)) {
-			r = -EINTR;
+			r = -ERESTARTSYS;
 			break;
 		}
 
